1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:02,399
The Cozy English.

2
00:00:02,399 --> 00:00:04,520
Learn English slowly.

3
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:06,700
Hi. Hi, everyone.

4
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:09,560
It's so lovely to be with you again.

5
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:10,819
I'm Emma.

6
00:00:10,819 --> 00:00:12,659
And I'm Daniel.

7
00:00:12,659 --> 00:00:14,160
Thanks for joining us.

8
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:17,935
It's always a joy to share this quiet space with you.

9
00:00:17,854 --> 00:00:19,775
How are you doing today?

10
00:00:20,014 --> 00:00:28,335
I hope you're feeling calm, maybe sipping something warm or just taking a peaceful break for yourself.

11
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:33,689
It's your little moment to breathe and reflect.

12
00:00:33,769 --> 00:00:35,130
I like that.

13
00:00:35,050 --> 00:00:36,970
A moment to breathe.

14
00:00:37,210 --> 00:00:40,250
I think we all need that more than we realize.

15
00:00:40,330 --> 00:00:48,085
Sometimes life feels like we're always running towards something, but we don't even know what that something really is.

16
00:00:48,324 --> 00:00:50,724
That's such a good way to put it.

17
00:00:50,885 --> 00:00:57,445
We often think becoming the best version of ourselves means arriving at a perfect point,

18
00:00:57,910 --> 00:01:02,950
having the right job, the right habits, the right mindset.

19
00:01:03,350 --> 00:01:08,469
But truthfully, becoming your best self isn't a destination.

20
00:01:08,710 --> 00:01:11,785
It's a journey that never stops.

21
00:01:11,785 --> 00:01:17,805
So it's not about reaching some final version of yourself, but continuing to grow.

22
00:01:17,725 --> 00:01:19,085
Exactly.

23
00:01:19,325 --> 00:01:21,165
Think of it like this.

24
00:01:21,325 --> 00:01:26,220
Every day, you're writing a new page in your own story.

25
00:01:26,620 --> 00:01:29,979
Some days are full of color and excitement.

26
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:33,579
Other days are quiet or even messy.

27
00:01:33,820 --> 00:01:36,299
But every page matters.

28
00:01:36,525 --> 00:01:38,204
That's comforting.

29
00:01:38,205 --> 00:01:41,804
Sometimes I feel like I should have figured everything out by now,

30
00:01:41,805 --> 00:01:46,524
but maybe I'm just in the middle of my story, and that's okay.

31
00:01:46,445 --> 00:01:48,604
That's more than okay.

32
00:01:48,845 --> 00:01:51,084
Growth is never a straight line.

33
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:57,579
It's full of small steps, mistakes, and moments of realization.

34
00:01:58,220 --> 00:02:04,219
Becoming your best self means learning, unlearning, and trying again.

35
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,499
I like that.

36
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:09,555
Learning, unlearning, and trying again.

37
00:02:09,875 --> 00:02:13,515
It sounds more forgiving than chasing perfection.

38
00:02:13,515 --> 00:02:15,394
It is forgiving.

39
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:18,994
The best version of you isn't perfect.

40
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:24,760
It's the version that keeps choosing to grow even when it's hard.

41
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:32,060
So maybe the goal isn't to arrive, but to stay curious about who we can still become.

42
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:34,159
Beautifully said, Daniel.

43
00:02:35,395 --> 00:02:44,115
When we stop rushing to arrive and start embracing the process, we discover something powerful.

44
00:02:44,595 --> 00:02:48,875
We're already becoming every single day.

45
00:02:48,875 --> 00:02:50,994
That makes me feel lighter.

46
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:55,609
Like I can take it one day at a time without pressure.

47
00:02:55,609 --> 00:02:58,609
That's exactly how it should feel.

48
00:02:58,930 --> 00:03:03,170
Becoming your best self isn't about racing forward.

49
00:03:03,555 --> 00:03:09,394
It's about waking up each day and saying, I'm still growing.

50
00:03:10,035 --> 00:03:15,634
Emma, I've been thinking about what you said, that becoming your best self is a journey.

51
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:21,580
I guess the next question is, how do we even know who that best self is?

52
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:24,760
That's such an important question, Daniel.

53
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:27,720
I think it starts with self awareness.

54
00:03:28,075 --> 00:03:35,355
Learning to look honestly at who you are, like standing in front of an inner mirror.

55
00:03:35,275 --> 00:03:36,595
Inner mirror.

56
00:03:36,595 --> 00:03:38,475
That's a powerful image.

57
00:03:38,395 --> 00:03:42,435
So it's not about how others see us, but how we see ourselves.

58
00:03:42,435 --> 00:03:43,274
Exactly.

59
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:48,019
We spend so much time adjusting our image for the world,

60
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:51,799
trying to be liked, to be right, to fit in.

61
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:57,159
But real growth begins when you can look at yourself without pretending,

62
00:03:57,455 --> 00:04:02,275
seeing your strengths and your flaws, and accepting both.

63
00:04:02,275 --> 00:04:04,975
That sounds hard sometimes.

64
00:04:04,895 --> 00:04:06,694
When I look at my own mistakes,

65
00:04:06,694 --> 00:04:11,015
I often feel guilty or disappointed even if I try to learn from them.

66
00:04:11,015 --> 00:04:12,334
And that's okay.

67
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:16,479
Self awareness isn't about judging yourself.

68
00:04:16,479 --> 00:04:19,440
It's about understanding yourself.

69
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:21,680
It's like cleaning a window.

70
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:25,280
At first, it's cloudy and uncomfortable.

71
00:04:25,359 --> 00:04:29,855
But once it clears, you see your life more truthfully.

72
00:04:29,855 --> 00:04:31,055
I like that image.

73
00:04:31,055 --> 00:04:32,535
Cleaning the window.

74
00:04:32,455 --> 00:04:36,895
Maybe that's why people say awareness is the first step to change.

75
00:04:36,895 --> 00:04:37,975
Yes.

76
00:04:37,974 --> 00:04:40,995
When you understand why you react,

77
00:04:40,995 --> 00:04:45,630
why you avoid something, or why you hold yourself back,

78
00:04:45,710 --> 00:04:48,830
you start to make better choices.

79
00:04:48,909 --> 00:04:51,669
You stop living on autopilot.

80
00:04:51,669 --> 00:04:53,210
I can relate to that.

81
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:56,670
There were times when I felt frustrated and didn't even know why.

82
00:04:56,825 --> 00:04:59,664
Once I started writing my thoughts in a journal,

83
00:04:59,664 --> 00:05:01,345
I realized I was chasing goals

84
00:05:01,345 --> 00:05:03,264
that didn't really belong to me.

85
00:05:03,264 --> 00:05:05,905
They were just things I thought I should want.

86
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:08,905
That's such a beautiful discovery.

87
00:05:09,289 --> 00:05:14,330
Sometimes the best version of ourselves isn't about adding more.

88
00:05:14,330 --> 00:05:17,530
It's about removing what doesn't belong.

89
00:05:17,609 --> 00:05:21,690
The expectations, the noise, the pressure.

90
00:05:21,594 --> 00:05:26,135
So becoming your best self isn't always about doing more,

91
00:05:26,135 --> 00:05:31,395
but about seeing clearly who you already are and what truly matters.

92
00:05:31,395 --> 00:05:32,315
Yes.

93
00:05:32,234 --> 00:05:35,675
And the mirror inside you doesn't lie.

94
00:05:35,594 --> 00:05:37,435
It shows what's real.

95
00:05:37,969 --> 00:05:47,450
When you can face yourself with honesty and kindness, you stop trying to be perfect, and you start being true.

96
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:48,870
That makes me think.

97
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:52,209
Maybe the best version of me isn't someone new.

98
00:05:52,335 --> 00:05:55,335
It's just me without the masks.

99
00:05:55,335 --> 00:05:58,394
That's a perfect way to say it, Daniel.

100
00:05:58,394 --> 00:06:04,255
When we learn to see ourselves clearly, that's when real growth begins.

101
00:06:04,255 --> 00:06:09,440
Not from outside approval, but from inner understanding.

102
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:16,880
Daniel, have you ever noticed how people often wait for the right moment to change?

103
00:06:17,039 --> 00:06:27,955
They wait for motivation, for the new year, for Monday, as if transformation only starts when life feels perfect.

104
00:06:27,955 --> 00:06:29,995
That's so true.

105
00:06:29,995 --> 00:06:37,020
I've done that so many times, telling myself, I'll start next week or when things calm down.

106
00:06:37,099 --> 00:06:40,580
But that perfect time never really comes, does it?

107
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:41,460
No.

108
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:42,619
It doesn't.

109
00:06:42,539 --> 00:06:46,220
The truth is change doesn't begin with motivation.

110
00:06:46,604 --> 00:06:50,365
It begins with small, consistent choices.

111
00:06:50,765 --> 00:06:56,445
It's less about waiting for the right mood and more about building the right habits.

112
00:06:56,364 --> 00:07:00,525
So, like, what kind of small choices?

113
00:07:00,445 --> 00:07:01,484
Simple ones.

114
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,100
Choosing to wake up a bit earlier,

115
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:09,720
to read instead of scroll, to speak kindly to yourself when things go wrong.

116
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:16,360
These small actions might look ordinary, but they build the foundation of who you're becoming.

117
00:07:16,414 --> 00:07:20,015
That reminds me of when I started exercising again.

118
00:07:19,935 --> 00:07:23,995
At first, I told myself I'd just do five minutes a day.

119
00:07:23,995 --> 00:07:27,815
It felt almost too easy, but it worked.

120
00:07:27,815 --> 00:07:31,454
Over time, those five minutes became thirty.

121
00:07:31,599 --> 00:07:34,240
That's a perfect example.

122
00:07:34,479 --> 00:07:37,840
The best version of you isn't built overnight.

123
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:42,720
It's shaped in quiet, daily choices that no one else sees.

124
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:48,305
Every small decision is a vote for the person you want to become.

125
00:07:48,305 --> 00:07:49,945
I like that idea.

126
00:07:49,945 --> 00:07:52,805
A vote for the person you want to become.

127
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:56,445
It turns small actions into something meaningful.

128
00:07:56,445 --> 00:07:57,345
Yes.

129
00:07:57,345 --> 00:08:08,459
When you choose progress over comfort, kindness over negativity, or discipline over excuses, you're rewriting your future in tiny steps.

130
00:08:08,459 --> 00:08:11,380
It's also less stressful that way.

131
00:08:11,299 --> 00:08:14,120
I used to think growth had to be dramatic,

132
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:17,285
like a total life change, but small,

133
00:08:17,285 --> 00:08:21,365
steady actions feel more real and more possible.

134
00:08:21,365 --> 00:08:23,244
That's the beauty of it.

135
00:08:23,164 --> 00:08:30,285
When you focus on small choices, you stop chasing perfection and start practicing improvement.

136
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:34,160
It's not about being someone new tomorrow.

137
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:37,480
It's about being 1% better today.

138
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:42,880
I think that's something our listeners will really relate to, especially those who feel stuck.

139
00:08:43,115 --> 00:08:47,235
It's a reminder that change doesn't need to be big to matter.

140
00:08:47,235 --> 00:08:48,235
Yes.

141
00:08:48,235 --> 00:08:52,154
Every small good decision is like a seed.

142
00:08:52,314 --> 00:08:54,475
It may take time to grow,

143
00:08:54,395 --> 00:08:56,730
but one day, you'll look back

144
00:08:56,730 --> 00:09:02,310
and realize those little choices built the best version of you.

145
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:09,329
That makes me want to start something small today, even if it's just one tiny promise to myself.

146
00:09:09,275 --> 00:09:12,235
And that's the perfect way to begin.

147
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:17,035
Because the best version of you isn't waiting somewhere far away.

148
00:09:17,194 --> 00:09:21,275
It's being built quietly right now.

149
00:09:21,834 --> 00:09:28,980
Emma, all this talk about small changes reminds me of people who completely turn their lives around.

150
00:09:28,980 --> 00:09:34,180
I've always wondered what really makes that kind of transformation possible.

151
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:36,260
That's a beautiful question.

152
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:42,875
I once met a woman named Leah who taught me a lot about real transformation.

153
00:09:43,275 --> 00:09:46,794
For years, she worked at a job she didn't love.

154
00:09:47,115 --> 00:09:55,010
Every day, she told herself she wasn't good enough to do anything else until one day, something small changed.

155
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:56,070
What happened?

156
00:09:56,070 --> 00:09:58,430
It was something ordinary, really.

157
00:09:58,430 --> 00:10:04,670
She was having coffee with a friend who asked, when was the last time you felt proud of yourself?

158
00:10:05,645 --> 00:10:08,925
That question stayed with her all night.

159
00:10:09,245 --> 00:10:15,805
The next morning, she looked in the mirror and realized she didn't recognize the person she'd become.

160
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:19,600
Always tired, always afraid.

161
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:23,840
That sounds heavy, but also like a turning point.

162
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:24,920
It was.

163
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,280
That day, she made a simple decision.

164
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:36,055
Not to quit her job, not to change everything, just to do one brave thing each day.

165
00:10:36,694 --> 00:10:40,215
Sometimes that meant saying no to extra work.

166
00:10:40,535 --> 00:10:44,715
Sometimes it meant applying for a course she'd always wanted.

167
00:10:44,715 --> 00:10:47,760
One brave thing each day.

168
00:10:48,079 --> 00:10:49,600
That's powerful.

169
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:54,360
It sounds small, but it slowly rewrites who you believe you are.

170
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,600
Exactly.

171
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:59,520
After a year, she didn't just have new skills.

172
00:10:59,439 --> 00:11:02,080
She had a new sense of self.

173
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:07,065
She said to me once, I didn't become a different person.

174
00:11:07,225 --> 00:11:09,725
I just stopped hiding the real one.

175
00:11:09,725 --> 00:11:12,585
That's such a beautiful line.

176
00:11:12,905 --> 00:11:17,225
It reminds me that transformation isn't about becoming someone else.

177
00:11:17,430 --> 00:11:22,510
It's about uncovering who you've always been underneath the fear.

178
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:23,510
Yes.

179
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:31,270
Real growth often looks quiet from the outside, but inside, it feels like the world opening up.

180
00:11:31,765 --> 00:11:33,925
It's not a sudden jump.

181
00:11:33,925 --> 00:11:35,964
It's a slow awakening.

182
00:11:35,964 --> 00:11:38,085
And it starts with courage.

183
00:11:38,005 --> 00:11:45,524
Not the loud kind, but the quiet courage to try again, to take one small step even when it's scary.

184
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:48,740
That's the kind that changes everything.

185
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:56,020
Leah's story reminds me that the best version of you isn't waiting for the perfect moment.

186
00:11:56,260 --> 00:12:00,965
It begins when you do something brave, no matter how small.

187
00:12:00,965 --> 00:12:04,445
I think that's something we can all carry with us.

188
00:12:04,525 --> 00:12:07,644
One small act of courage each day.

189
00:12:07,725 --> 00:12:13,990
It makes the idea of becoming your best self feel less like a dream and more like a choice.

190
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:15,070
Yes.

191
00:12:15,069 --> 00:12:19,870
Because in the end, transformation doesn't happen overnight.

192
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:26,990
It happens every time you choose to believe there's more in you than your fear wants you to see.

193
00:12:28,355 --> 00:12:35,795
Daniel, I think the most important part of becoming your best self is remembering this.

194
00:12:36,194 --> 00:12:38,755
It's not about being perfect.

195
00:12:38,995 --> 00:12:43,160
It's about being better, a little at a time.

196
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,960
That's true.

197
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:52,880
I used to think the best version of me meant always positive, always strong, never making mistakes.

198
00:12:53,535 --> 00:13:00,015
But now I realize that kind of perfection just makes you tired and afraid to be real.

199
00:13:01,295 --> 00:13:03,854
I love how you said that.

200
00:13:04,495 --> 00:13:07,695
Real growth doesn't mean never falling.

201
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:12,909
It means learning to stand up with more grace each time.

202
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:16,030
You don't need to shine every day.

203
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:19,789
Some days, you just need to show up.

204
00:13:19,949 --> 00:13:22,110
That's such a relief to hear.

205
00:13:22,824 --> 00:13:29,945
I think people sometimes forget that becoming your best self also means accepting your worst moments,

206
00:13:29,944 --> 00:13:33,145
learning from them instead of running away.

207
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:34,585
Yes.

208
00:13:34,665 --> 00:13:41,060
The best version of you knows how to rest, forgive, and keep going.

209
00:13:41,540 --> 00:13:48,120
It's the version that chooses kindness over judgment, especially toward yourself.

210
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:50,339
That's something I'm still learning.

211
00:13:50,805 --> 00:13:54,965
When I fail, my first instinct is to be harsh with myself.

212
00:13:55,045 --> 00:13:59,885
But lately, I've been trying to ask, what can I learn from this?

213
00:13:59,885 --> 00:14:02,185
Instead of what's wrong with me.

214
00:14:02,185 --> 00:14:04,085
That's growth, Daniel.

215
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:13,430
It's the voice of self compassion, the quiet strength that helps you become not only better, but happier.

216
00:14:13,430 --> 00:14:23,865
So maybe the best version of ourselves isn't about doing everything right, but about doing things with more heart.

217
00:14:23,865 --> 00:14:25,205
Exactly.

218
00:14:26,245 --> 00:14:34,645
Growth looks different for everyone, but it always begins with love, patience, and courage.

219
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:39,799
The kind of courage that whispers, keep going.

220
00:14:40,199 --> 00:14:42,200
You're doing fine.

221
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:45,880
That's something I want our listeners to remember too.

222
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:52,095
You don't need to wait for a perfect day or a perfect version of yourself.

223
00:14:52,015 --> 00:14:55,875
You're already becoming just by trying.

224
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:56,975
Yes.

225
00:14:56,975 --> 00:15:01,295
And the best version of you isn't someone you have to find.

226
00:15:01,615 --> 00:15:10,010
It's someone you already are, just waiting to be cared for, understood, and trusted.

227
00:15:10,329 --> 00:15:16,810
To everyone listening, thank you for sharing this quiet time with us today.

228
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:22,810
We hope this episode reminded you that growth doesn't need to be big or fast.

229
00:15:23,475 --> 00:15:26,195
It just needs to be honest.

230
00:15:26,194 --> 00:15:31,075
Take one small step each day, no matter how simple.

231
00:15:31,235 --> 00:15:37,474
Read something new, take a walk, forgive yourself, or just breathe.

232
00:15:38,449 --> 00:15:40,770
That's how you keep becoming.

233
00:15:40,770 --> 00:15:47,250
Remember, you don't have to be perfect, just present.

234
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:51,729
You're already enough, and your journey matters.

235
00:15:52,015 --> 00:15:55,295
Keep believing in the person you're becoming.

236
00:15:55,535 --> 00:15:57,574
You're doing better than you think.

237
00:15:57,574 --> 00:16:01,375
Thank you for listening to the cozy English.

238
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:05,855
Take care of yourself, and keep growing gently.

239
00:16:07,090 --> 00:16:09,329
See you next time, friends.

240
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:12,330
Bye bye, and have a peaceful day.

241
00:16:12,330 --> 00:16:13,050
Bye bye.
